        <h1>Surya Teja Pidakala</h1>
        <h2>Effects of Privatization on Space Missions</h2>
        <p>Uncovering the changes occurred to the industry of Space Mission over time as Private industry set foot into the field </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Analyze the impact of privatization on space missions, focusing on private companies like SpaceX, Blue Origin, and Virgin Galactic.</li>
            <li>Privatization has brought innovation, cost-efficiency, and increased commercial opportunities, accelerating space exploration.</li>
            <li>Utilized datasets from The Center for Strategic and International Studies and NASA; used Tableau for visualizations.</li>
            <li>Key Findings:
                  Decrease in mission failure rates since 2004.
                  Reduced cost per kilogram for space launches.
                  Increased number of space missions, especially post-2016.</li>
        </ul>
